The net present value of a project determines whether the project is profitable or not. A positive net present value means that the project will bring profits while a negative value will not be profitable. The net present value acn be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Net present value}&=-\text{Operating cash flow} \times \text{annuity factor}\\
&-\text{Initial cost}
\end{aligned}$$

For the operating cash flow, we can solve it using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Operating cash flow}&=\text{Operating cost}\times (1-\text{Tax rate})\\
&+\dfrac{\text{Cost for A}}{\text{Lifespan}}\times \text{Tax rate}
\end{aligned}$$
